answers.answer: Hi,How are you? Aside from the urine odor, what other symptoms are present? What medications are you taking presently? Changes in urine odor  may be attributed to certain foods and medicines. However,  if this persists, this may warrant further evaluation by a doctor to rule out  infection, diabetes,  liver disease, certain metabolic disorders and other underlying medical conditions. Take care and do keep us posted.
